node.text: Lucia and Agustin of @proyectopasillodeco's home used to belong to Lucia's grandparents and looked nothing like it does today. The pair made the space much brighter by getting rid of the dark, old wallpaper, and then got to work transforming each room one DIY at a time. They did such a great job, it's no wonder they were crowned our 2021 Small/Cool contest winners! 👑

node.text: Music teacher @kirstymarie23’s New York studio is remarkably functional and cozy despite the small size! Kirsten and her dad added a backsplash over the oven, painted and hung cabinets, built a loft, retiled the bathroom floor, added a sink to the basin of the toilet, as well as many other small fixes/additions here and there. “Together, we made it great, and it feels like a true New York Apartment,” she says.
